Date: Sat, 11 Jul 2026 20:43:27 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat: show real avatars on Dashboard and Metrics pages

v1.9.6 threaded avatarUrl through the Activity page's recentActivity
feed, but three other surfaces build user objects from separate code
paths that were missed:
- Metrics page User Leaderboard + Watch Streaks (watchActivity.byUser)
- Dashboard Recent Activity (recentActivity, already had the data
  server-side but the component wasn't passing it to UserAvatar)
- Dashboard Top Viewers (also watchActivity.byUser)

Added avatarUrl/useGravatar to the watchActivityByUser init in
metricsBuilder.js, and threaded it through all four frontend call
sites (including UserStreaksList, which needed the field added to its
own props/types since it renders from a prop, not a direct API call).

Bump to 1.9.7, changelog entry added.
